Is there disproportionate education attainment by race in the county? Answer: Based on the data from San Mateo County, there is a disproportionate education attainment by race for individuals 25 years or older. In white race population, there is a significant more proportion of individuals that have some college or bachelors degree than lss than high school diploma. When you compare white alone to black or African American alone, there is a disproportionate education attainment. The proportion of black individuals holding bachelors degree or higher is far less than high school graduate. The situation is the opposite in white individuals. American Indian and Alaska Native alone does not face disproportionate education attainment. In Asian alone population, there is a greater proportion of individuals that have bachelors degree or higher than the three other educational categories.
